&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Inventory Control Associate is responsible for overseeing and managing inventory to ensure the efficient and accurate tracking of all inventory-related activities. This role includes monitoring stock levels, reconciling discrepancies, and implementing procedures to optimize inventory control. The Inventory Control Specialist plays a key role in maintaining the balance between stock availability and minimizing excess inventory, contributing to the overall efficiency and profitability of the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain precise inventory records and update data as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize computer systems and digital tools effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor stock levels and conduct regular inventory checks and audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform cycle counting to ensure the accuracy of inventory records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and resolve inventory discrepancies, identifying and addressing underlying issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with various departments to ensure accurate order processing and inventory management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the receipt of materials and oversee quality checks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address defective goods by coordinating returns and processing supplier credits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with shipping products to customers and support other inventory-related tasks as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience with an ERP software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills and Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of lifting up to 50 lbs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work varying hours, including weekends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years of relevant experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
